Welcome Marcella “Ms. Lago” Araica to the @ohio.university Music Industry Summit lineup! Araica is an award-winning recording and mixing engineer and co-founder of New Age Rock Stars record label and Dream Asylum Studios. She is responsible for numerous multiplatinum smashes and has worked with top artists including Beyoncé, Britney Spears, DJ Khaled, Mariah Carey, Timbaland, and many more.⚡️ Don’t miss hearing from this legend at this year’s Summit! 

In-person and virtual options available to anyone for free. Register➡️ link in bio!

Here’s a real #tbt for you.  #otd in 2002 we were working on some demos for a new @missymisdemeanorelliott album.  All six studios were packed and we needed an assistant for the Missy session. There was a intern at the time with a great attitude spending off hours in the rooms and generally going the extra mile. 

Gave her the gig and some 21 years later, and @incrediblelago is still at it.  She even comes here to work every so often!

Introducing our latest #STMAmbassador, Marcella Araica—an accomplished music producer and engineer celebrated for her role in crafting chart-topping hits for iconic artists like Keri Hilson, Britney Spears, Keyshia Cole, Meek Mill, M.I.A., Usher, Wiz Khalifa, and Madonna.

Beyond her achievements, Araica is a powerful advocate for music education. She firmly believes that music isn’t solely an art form; it’s a pivotal tool that nurtures students on a spiritual, emotional, and intellectual level. Today, she generously shares insights into her musical journey, shedding light on her success!

@incrediblelago @Kerihilson @britneyspears keyshiacole @meekmill @miamatangi @usher @wizkhalifa @madonna @fullsail 

#music #musicsaves #musiceducation #studentsuccess #miami #artistsoninstagram #savethemusic #communityspotlight #musicproduction #sounddesign

We are SO inspired by our #STMAmbassador Marcella Araica's unwavering support for music education. 🙌

Since her early years, Marcella's connection with music has played a crucial role in shaping her identity. The combination of Miami's distinctive sounds and her cultural upbringing from an early age ignited her creative passion. It sparked a successful, award-winning future as a recording and mixing engineer. Today, Marcella speaks to empowering students through music in schools. Let's support Miami's youth and save the music! 

@incrediblelago
